      "writtenOn": "2016-11-09T18:44:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Will clustering ever produce more than one low or high regression? E.g. a bunch of tests are 10% slower, and a bunch of other tests are 5x slower -- would that end up as two clusters?\n\nIf not, how is it possible that we would have both a low and a high cluster, since it seems to be the same algorithm whether it\u0027s a step up or step down?\n\nIf so, how would that be indicated in the UI and stored in Regression below?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 49,
        "startChar": 31,
        "endLine": 49,
        "endChar": 72
      },
      "revId": "1e1649b0f31c56b8071a6189b1ffb0141e73fa38",
